EU Commission proposes new court in dispute over TTIP
The EU Commission has proposed a comprehensive reform of the current arbitration system to address the dispute over the proposed TTIP Transatlantic Free Trade Agreement.
The controversial private arbitration bodies for disputes between corporations and states are therefore to be replaced by a more transparent system, which in its functioning corresponds to significantly more traditional courts.
“We want to set up a system that citizens trust,” EU Commissioner Cecilia Malmström said at the event.
Sweden intends to include the proposal as a European negotiating position in the free trade talks with the US.
