TTIP aims to create the largest free trade zone in the world with 800 million people.
The plans to reform the current arbitration procedures provide specifically for the EU states and the US to jointly elect independent judges for a new investment court.
They are supposed to come from the EU, the US and third countries in equal parts.
For the first time, there is also a second instance.
